Creating images with R

with a little bit of magick

Peng-Chong Chen

2023-03-10

Introduction of my meme creation and my gif creation

My meme shows a situation I often encounter when I’m doing my assignment: the computer says it automatically saved my document but I can’t find it. The result of this situation is that I need to do my assignment again. My gif is also based on my meme.

library(magick)
# read a image from the Internet
computer_meme <- image_read(path = "https://memeprod.ap-south-1.linodeobjects.com/user-template/63e160366afc7f7a7a1e5de55fd0e38f.png")
# generate a new image
computer_meme_text <- image_blank(width = 599, # size
                                  height = 567, # size
                                  color = "#001a4d") %>%
  # add text
  image_annotate(text = "My computer:\nSaved the document\nautomatically\nMe:\nGreat!\nSo where is it?\nMy computer:",
                 color = "#f2f2f2",
                 size = 60,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")
# composite image
top_meme <- image_append(c(computer_meme_text, computer_meme))
# read another image from the Internet
meo_meme <- image_read(path = "https://pbs.twimg.com/media/FiKmZRyVUAARhW8.jpg")
# generate a new image
meo_meme_text <- image_blank(width = 600,
                             height = 600,
                             color = "#4d4d4d") %>%
  # add text
  image_annotate(text = "When I searched\nfor an hour and\nstill couldn't find\nthe document I needed",
                 color = "#f2f2f2",
                 size = 60,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")
# composite image
bottom_meme <- image_append(c(meo_meme_text, meo_meme))
# composite the whole meme
my_meme <- c(top_meme, bottom_meme) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE) %>%
  image_write("my_meme.png") # save the meme

My meme

library(magick)
# read a image from the Internet
computer_meme <- image_read(path = "https://memeprod.ap-south-1.linodeobjects.com/user-template/63e160366afc7f7a7a1e5de55fd0e38f.png")
# generate a new image
computer_meme_text <- image_blank(width = 599, # size
                                  height = 567, # size
                                  color = "#001a4d") %>%
  # add text
  image_annotate(text = "My computer:\nSaved the document\nautomatically\nMe:\nGreat!\nSo where is it?\nMy computer:",
                 color = "#f2f2f2",
                 size = 60,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")
# composite image
top_meme <- image_append(c(computer_meme_text, computer_meme))
# read another image from the Internet
meo_meme <- image_read(path = "https://pbs.twimg.com/media/FiKmZRyVUAARhW8.jpg")
# generate a new image
meo_meme_text <- image_blank(width = 600,
                             height = 600,
                             color = "#4d4d4d") %>%
  # add text
  image_annotate(text = "When I searched\nfor an hour and\nstill couldn't find\nthe document I needed",
                 color = "#f2f2f2",
                 size = 60,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")
# composite image
bottom_meme <- image_append(c(meo_meme_text, meo_meme))
# composite the whole meme
my_meme <- c(top_meme, bottom_meme) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE) %>%
  image_write("my_meme.png") # save the meme
# combine all the frames
frame <- c(computer_meme_text, computer_meme, meo_meme_text, meo_meme)
# make a gif
my_gif <- image_animate(frame, fps = 1) %>%
  image_write("my_animation.gif") # save the animation gif
